he classloader handles already loaded dependencies. It’s a bit tricky!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering dynamic class loading**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the approach of using open-ended dynamic class loading instead of direct reflection. The testing seems tricky, especially with potential exceptions thrown for URLs. The user mentioned not to compile or run the code, which gives me pause. I feel like retaining raw bytes would be a wise choice to keep everything broad. Also, I think removing the isolated `defineClass` and `Base64` constant will help keep the file organized and manageable.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_NDRWN2357jEDi7qGaC8erc0C|fc_0606207fb2c57cb00169f50ed22448819c995e747b1d91963f", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\np=Path('tests/src/javax.mail/mail/1.4/src/test/java/javax_mail/mail/MessageRfc822Test.java')\ntext=p.read_text()\n# remove Base64 import\ntext=text.replace('import java.util.Base64;\\n', '')\n# add imports after StandardCharsets\ntext=text.replace('import java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\\n', 'import java.net.URL;\\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;\\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\\nimport java.security.CodeSource;\\n')\n# remove huge bytes constant\nstart=text.index('    private static final String MESSAGE_RFC822_HANDLER_BYTES = \"\"\"\\n')\nend=text.index('            \"\"\";\\n', start)+len('            \"\"\";\\n')\ntext=text[:start]+text[end:]\n# replace isolated test\nold='''    @Test\\n    void initializesIsolatedMessageHandlerThroughActivationCommandMap() {\\n        IsolatedMessageRfc822ClassLoader classLoader = new IsolatedMessageRfc822ClassLoader(parentClassLoader());\\n        Thread currentThread = Thread.currentThread();\\n        ClassLoader originalContextClassLoader = currentThread.getContextClassLoader();\\n        currentThread.setContextClassLoader(classLoader);\\n        try {\\n            DataFlavor[] flavors = getTransferDataFlavors(new MessageDataSource(MESSAGE_TEXT), new MailcapCommandMap());\\n\\n            assertMessageFlavor(flavors);\\n            assertThat(classLoader.isHandlerClassDefined()).isTrue();\\n        } catch (Error error) {\\n            rethrowUnlessUnsupportedDynamicClassLoading(error);\\n        } finally {\\n            currentThread.setContextClassLoader(originalContextClassLoader);\\n        }\\n    }\\n'''\nnew='''    @Test\\n    void initializesMessageHandlerLoadedFromArtifactThroughActivationCommandMap() throws Exception {\\n        CodeSource codeSource = message_rfc822.class.getProtectionDomain().getCodeSource();\\n        MessageHandlerClassLoader classLoader = new MessageHandlerClassLoader(\\n                new URL[] {codeSource.getLocation()}, parentClassLoader());\\n        Thread currentThread = Thread.currentThread();\\n        ClassLoader originalContextClassLoader = currentThread.getContextClassLoader();\\n        currentThread.setContextClassLoader(classLoader);\\n        try {\\n            DataFlavor[] flavors = getTransferDataFlavors(new MessageDataSource(MESSAGE_TEXT), new MailcapCommandMap());\\n\\n            assertMessageFlavor(flavors);\\n            assertThat(classLoader.isHandlerClassLoaded()).isTrue();\\n        } catch (Error error) {\\n            rethrowUnlessUnsupportedDynamicClassLoading(error);\\n        } finally {\\n            currentThread.setContextClassLoader(originalContextClassLoader);\\n            classLoader.close();\\n        }\\n    }\\n'''\nif old not in text:\n    raise SystemExit('old isolated test not found')\ntext=text.replace(old,new)\n# replace class loader class\nold='''    private static final class IsolatedMessageRfc822ClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\\n        private Class<?> handlerClass;\\n\\n        private IsolatedMessageRfc822ClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\\n            super(parent);\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\\n            if (!MESSAGE_RFC822_HANDLER_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\\n                return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\\n            }\\n            Class<?> loadedClass = handlerClass;\\n            if (loadedClass == null) {\\n                byte[] bytes = Base64.getMimeDecoder().decode(MESSAGE_RFC822_HANDLER_BYTES);\\n                loadedClass = defineClass(name, bytes, 0, bytes.length, DataHandler.class.getProtectionDomain());\\n                handlerClass = loadedClass;\\n            }\\n            if (resolve) {\\n                resolveClass(loadedClass);\\n            }\\n            return loadedClass;\\n        }\\n\\n        private boolean isHandlerClassDefined() {\\n            return handlerClass != null;\\n        }\\n    }\\n'''\nnew='''    private static final class MessageHandlerClassLoader extends URLClassLoader {\\n        private boolean handlerClassLoaded;\\n\\n        private MessageHandlerClassLoader(URL[] urls, ClassLoader parent) {\\n            super(urls, parent);\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\\n            if (!MESSAGE_RFC822_HANDLER_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\\n                return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\\n            }\\n            synchronized (getClassLoadingLock(name)) {\\n                Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\\n                if (loadedClass == null) {\\n                    loadedClass = findClass(name);\\n                    handlerClassLoaded = true;\\n                }\\n                if (resolve) {\\n                    resolveClass(loadedClass);\\n                }\\n                return loadedClass;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        private boolean isHandlerClassLoaded() {\\n            return handlerClassLoaded;\\n        }\\n    }\\n'''\nif old not in text:\n    raise SystemExit('old class loader not found')\ntext=text.replace(old,new